    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The report that the Clearwater\nriver from Lewiston up had been\ndeclared unnavigable by the gov\neminent, and therefore could not\nbe utilized for mill sites, dams and\nwater powers for manufacturing\nplants and other purposes, is not\ncorrect, says Brig. Gen. A. Mac\nKinzie, chief of engineers of the\nUnited States army, in an indorse-\nment on the back of a letter of in\nquiry from U. S. Senator Fred T.\nDubois directed to the war depart\nment."
    }
